definition.value: A  hydroxy monocarboxylic acid anion that is the conjugate base of SN-38 carboxylic acid, obtained from the deprotonation of the carboxy group. It is the major microspecies at pH 7.3.
A dialkyl ketone that is hexane in which the two methylene protons at position 3 have been replaced by an oxo group.
A member of the class of furoic acids that is 2-furoic acid substituted at position 5 by a methyl group.
A bile acid glycine conjugate derived from ursoodeoxycholic acid.
